Tide was so low this past winter that my boat lift could not lower enough to allow my boat to float off of it, and I tried reversing it off the lift a few times, without success.. instead of putting it into neutral, I put it into reverse idle(accidentally) … getting off the boat made it lighter, and the consistent idling probably was enough to get the boat to float off the lift.. and here’s what followed 😂

I know the online critics are salivating waiting to type something, but I find it too funny not to share 😂👍🏼
In the end, we’ll be more disappointed in the things we didn’t do, rather than the things we did

I’m very happy to announce that we have started a new company, Rise Construction. We have already built quite a team, and although we are a new company, we offer experience in a wide range of services. 

At Rise, our goal is making your vision of your home, a reality. Kitchen remodeling, Bathroom remodeling and Interior Design are currently our main focus, although we are offering exterior services including Windows/Doors, Soffits/Gutters and Stucco as well. 

https://riseconstructionfl.com/

Side Note: I will still be overseeing operations at Greenwell Painting, the management of the company is still in good hands.
